author: CNN
description: Police say more than 1,000 people gathered in London’s Parliament Square on Saturday to protest the British government’s decision to ban the activist group Palestine Action. The UK-based network uses vandalism and other means to disrupt the operations of weapons manufacturers it says are linked to the Israeli government.
title: Police arrest protesters in London’s Parliament Square

author: CNN
description:
US President Donald Trump posted a meme on Truth Social that appeared to be an artificially generated image of Trump with the Chicago skyline as the city braces for an immigration crackdown and after the president signed an executive order on Friday to rebrand the Pentagon as the "Department of War."  
US Representative Mike Qigley, Illinois Democrat joins CNN's Jessica Dean for a discussion.
 #CNN #News
title: Trump on Truth Social: 'Chicago about to find out why it’s called the Department of WAR’

author: CNN
description: US President Donald Trump told reporters on Friday that some of the 20 hostages who are presumed to be alive in Gaza may have “recently died.” The president did not reveal the source of the information regarding the possible deaths, and comes as Israel has expanded an assault on Gaza City.    #CNN #News
title: Trump says some hostages may have ‘recently died’ in Gaza

title: E.A. Hanks on family, fame, and surviving her mother’s abuse

description: A 57-year-old man was killed in a shark attack while surfing in Sydney, the city’s first fatal incident in over three years. Beaches were closed as a precaution. #cnn #shark #sydneyaustralia #surfing
title: Shark attack kills Sydney surfer

author: CNN
description:
A sprawling Hyundai manufacturing plant in a quiet southeast Georgia community became ground zero on Thursday for one of the most extensive immigration raids in recent US history. The operation, months in the making, ended with 475 arrests, most of them Korean nationals.

South Korea’s President Lee Jae Myung told officials to take “all-out necessary measures” to support Korean nationals, Cho said following an emergency meeting in Seoul over the arrests.

“If necessary, I am prepared to personally travel to Washington, DC, to engage directly with US officials to resolve this matter,” Cho said.

The Korean Ambassador to the US and the Consul General in Atlanta had established an on-site response team that will “assess countermeasures, emphasizing the rights of our citizens and the economic activities of Korean businesses investing in the US must be protected from unfair violations,” Cho added.

CNN correspondents Rafael Romo and Mike Valerio report.

 #CNN #News
title: 475 arrested in massive immigration raid at Georgia Hyundai plant

description:
South Korean President Lee Jae Myung vowed “all-out necessary measures” to support the more than 300 Korean nationals ICE detained at a manufacturing plant in Georgia on Thursday. CNN’s Mike Valerio breaks down how the country plans to respond.

#CNN #News #ICE #SouthKorea

author: CNN
description:
The latest jobs report, released Friday, indicated that the US economy added about 22,000 jobs in August and the unemployment rate ticked up to 4.3%, the highest it's been in nearly four years.

The unemployment rate for Black workers in the United States rose again last month to 7.5%, the highest level since October 2021. A rise in the Black unemployment rate is often considered "the canary in the coal mine," foretelling a broader-scale job market slowdown.

CNN's Victor Blackwell discusses with his "First of All" panel: Black Voters Matter Fund co-founder LaTosha Brown, former GOP Georgia Senate candidate Stephanie Donegan, and Capital B national editor Dalila Paul. #CNN #News
title: Economy warning sign: Number of unemployed Black women grows

author: CNN
description:

CNN's Victor Blackwell speaks with Stacy Davis Gates, president of the Chicago Teachers Union. #CNN #News
title: Chicago teachers give students flyers listing their rights

author: CNN
description:

CNN's Anderson Cooper speaks with David Phillipps a national correspondent from The New York Times.   #CNN #News
title: NYT: Trump greenlit 2019 failed Seal Team 6 mission into North Korea

author: CNN
description:
Russian President Vladimir Putin said that any Western troops in Ukraine would be considered “legitimate targets for defeat,” a day after it was announced that dozens of Western countries have pledged to contribute to a potential peacekeeping force there if a ceasefire deal is agreed.
CNN's Jim Sciutto is joined by Max Bermann, Europe, Russia & Eurasia Program Director, CSIS for a discussion.  #CNN #News
title: Putin says Western troops would be ‘legitimate targets’ if they are in Ukraine

author: CNN
description:
The White House says it plans to roll back proposed rules by the Biden administration, including some that required passengers to be compensated by airlines for disrupted flights.

According to a public document posted Thursday by the White House, the Department of Transportation will withdraw an advanced notice of proposed rulemaking that explored the idea of requiring US and foreign air carriers to provide “essential services,” and compensation to passengers after a canceled or delayed flight in the US due to circumstances within the airline’s control. #CNN #News
title: WH to abandon rules that compensate customers for disrupted flights
